dcterms:description: The SelfExp method is a statistical approach for outlier detection in data cubes, utilizing a trimmed mean to compute an outlierness score based on the deviation of actual values from estimated values.
dcterms:title: SelfExp method

dcterms:creator: L. Breiman
dcterms:description: The Random Forest (RF) method is an ensemble learning technique that constructs multiple decision trees for regression tasks, providing robust predictions and is used in the RODD-RF approach for estimating values in data cubes.
dcterms:title: Random Forest (RF)

dcterms:description: Random Search is a hyperparameter optimization technique used in machine learning, specifically mentioned in the context of tuning the Random Forest model for the RODD-RF method.
